HEADWORD: Orthoxylene
<hw>Or`tho*xy"lene</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Ortho-</ets> + <ets>xylene</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>That variety of xylene (<chform>C6H4(CH3)2</chform>) in which the
two methyl groups are in the <xex>ortho</xex> position; a colorless,
liquid, combustible hydrocarbon resembling benzene.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ortive</ent>⟦br⟧
